eed all of its genes!  A possible cause for these extra genes might be a more complex immune response in human beings where its found.  It might also be because of the symbiotic requirements of insects is simpler.  <\/p>\n","answer_id":13922,"question_id":13905,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1386870521}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/13905/what-is-the-most-genetically-simple-organism-except-viruses","last_activity_date":1386870521,"creation_date":1386693475,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is the most genetically simple organism except viruses?","body":"<p>What is the most genetically simple organism (except viruses) on this planet?<\/p>\n\n<p>By simple I mean the least number of genes.<\/p>\n","question_id":13905,"tags":["dna","genetics","chromosome"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":13922,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":271,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1386694443},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/99108b7e3ffda7434234140e552c6674?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4254,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4254/greek-fellows","reputation":621,"display_name":"Greek Fellows","accept_rate":73},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cb0d3bf434b794176466f428a6d681db?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4136,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4136/mys-721tx","reputation":105,"display_name":"Mys_721tx"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/99108b7e3ffda7434234140e552c6674?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4254,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4254/greek-fellows","reputation":621,"display_name":"Greek Fellows","accept_rate":73},"score":0,"post_id":13921,"edited":false,"creation_date":1386948169,"comment_id":18271,"body":"similar to migration of leukocytes to inflammatory sites... so you mean it&#