mproved core packing, shorter and/or tighter surface loops, enhanced secondary structure propensities, or oligomerization.\"<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Also, everything I have seen about the genus thermus places them as Gram negative bacteria.<\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2242557/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Razvi and Scholtz. Lessons in stability from thermophilic proteins. Protein Science, 15(7) 2006.<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","answer_id":13881,"question_id":13879,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/13879/why-is-thermus-aquaticus-and-taq-pol-stable","last_activity_date":1386531573,"creation_date":1386528541,"answer_count":1,"title":"Why is Thermus aquaticus and Taq Pol stable?","body":"<p>What is the molecular basis of the stability of the bacterium Thermus aquaticus and the enzyme Taq Pol it produces ?<\/p>\n\n<p>I have tried googling this but did not get a good answer.<\/p>\n","question_id":13879,"tags":["biochemistry","bacteriology","adaptation"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":13881,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":76,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8fbbdee11e60637a80fe74d6f3b747fd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":5008,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5008/munish","reputation":283,"display_name":"munish","accept_rate":75},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef6c1e9a540c28587fe777f9bcf907af?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1231,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1231/mcm","reputation":7783,"display_name":"MCM"},"score":2,"post_id":13720,"edited":false,"creation_date":1385784973,"comment_id":17909,"body":"Question: What makes you think it&#39;s the deviated septum instead of different cold strains?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8fbbdee11e60637a80fe74d6f3b747fd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type