s are taken as given and the logic is built on them. You need to accept certain things as premises in order to construct your logic. In a philosophical discussion, I am willing to accept that my perceived reality is likely not real. I cannot accept that premise for a scientific argument or for my day-to-day life though, because that way lies madness."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1MUb2.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1306,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1306/terdon","reputation":9339,"display_name":"terdon","accept_rate":73},"score":1,"post_id":13566,"edited":false,"creation_date":1384899550,"comment_id":17612,"body":"Why is it that at least 7 people have voted on answers but only I have voted on the question? Whether we agree with their worldview or not, the OP has asked a perfectly valid question in a non-confrontational manner and deserves an upvote. We should not refrain from upvoting valid questions just because we have a philosophical disagreement with the OP."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/934a90404fe944a01135142de991d393?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4199,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4199/von-mises","reputation":746,"display_name":"von Mises"},"score":0,"post_id":13566,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1MUb2.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1306,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1306/terdon","reputation":9339,"display_name":"terdon","accept_rate":73},"edited":false,"creation_date":1385570299,"comment_id":17840,"body":"@terdon - I dont think it was a good question. For starters the title is &quot;Why is there such an argument about evolution&quot; but thats not what he is asking at all. Indeed, what he is asking is clear as mud. He first asks about how / if (?) genes can influence behavior. Not a bad biology question, but then he asks about why scientists ignore this, whi